definitions.definition: Belonging to, or proceeding from, angels ; resembling, characteristic of, or partaking of the nature of, an angel .
Of or pertaining to angelic acid .
A regular Hausdorff space is said to be angelic if the closure of each relatively countably compact set A is compact and the closure consists of the limits of sequences in A .

main_definition: Belonging to, or proceeding from, angels ; resembling, characteristic of, or partaking of the nature of, an angel .
